modules.description: This module enables typed configuration parameter declaration, command-line argument parsing, and documentation generation for structured data handling. It operates on configuration parameters, string-based input values, and documentation blocks, supporting conversions to primitive types, enums, file paths, and composite structures like lists and tuples with customizable separators. Typical use cases include parsing program options, validating user-provided values, and producing structured manpage documentation from configuration metadata.

This module provides logging and progress reporting capabilities, working with formatted messages and optional metadata such as task names, stages, and totals. It supports typed configuration handling through its Config submodule, which processes command-line arguments, validates values, and generates documentation for structured data like enums, lists, and file paths. Concrete use cases include parsing and documenting program options, reporting execution progress with contextual notes, and ensuring configuration correctness through typed declarations.
